Braintree, MA Business Real Estate Lodging History

The community of Braintree is located only ten miles south of Boston. Because of Braintree’s proximity to Boston, it has become an ideal place for industrial parks and offices. Braintree, Massachusetts is home to the South Shore Plaza, one of the largest shopping plazas in the northeast region. Not only is Braintree full of commercial activity, but it also thrives on it. John Hancock, John Adams, and John Quincy Adams were all born in Braintree. A more current notable resident is William Rosenberg, the creator of Dunkin’ Donuts.
